quran[20]{c,v,t}:
  3,133,"And vie with one another for pardon from your Lord, and for Paradise, the breadth of which is as the heaven and the earth, prepared for those who fear"
  3,134,"for those who expend in alms, in prosperity and adversity, for those who repress their rage, and those who pardon men; God loves the kind"
  3,135,"Those who when they do a crime, or wrong themselves, remember God, and ask forgiveness for their sins,- and who forgives sins save God?- and do not persevere in what they did, the while they know"
  3,136,"these have their reward:- pardon from their Lord, and gardens beneath which rivers flow, dwelling therein for aye; for pleasant is the hire of those who act like this"
  3,137,"Incidents have passed before your time, go on then in the earth, and see what was the end of those who called (the prophets) liars"
  3,138,"This is an explanation unto men, and a guidance and a warning unto those who fear"
  3,139,"Do not give way nor grieve, for ye shall have the upper hand if ye but be believers"
  3,140,"If a sore touch you, a sore like it has touched people: these are days which we make to alternate amongst mankind that God may know who it is that believe, and may take from you witnesses, for God loves not the unjust"
  3,141,"and that God may assay those who believe, and blot out the misbelievers"
  3,142,"Do ye think that ye can enter Paradise and God not know those of you who have fought well, or know the patient"
  3,143,"Why, ye longed for death before ye met it! Now ye have looked upon it and ye halt"
  3,144,"Mohammed is but an apostle; apostles have passed away before his time; what if he die or is killed, will ye retreat upon your heels? He who retreats upon his heels does no harm to God at all; but God will recompense the thankful"
  3,145,"It is not for any soul to die, save by God's permission written down for an appointed time; but he who wishes for the reward of this world we will give him of it, and he who wishes for the reward of the future we will give him of it, and we will recompense the grateful"
  3,146,"How many prophets have myriads fought against! yet they did not give way at what befel them in God's way Nor were they weak, nor did they demean themselves:- God loves the patient"
  3,147,"And their word was only to say, 'Lord, forgive us our sins and our extravagance in our affairs; and make firm our footing, and help us against the misbelieving folk"
  3,148,"and God gave them the reward of this world, and good reward for the future too, for God doth love the kind"
  3,149,"O ye who believe! if ye obey those who misbelieve, they will turn you back upon your heels, and ye will retreat the losers"
  3,150,"Nay, God is your Lord, He is the best of helpers"
  3,151,"We will throw dread into the hearts of those who misbelieve, for that they associate that with God which He has sent down no power for; but their resort is fire, and evil is the resort of the unjust"
  3,152,"God has truly kept His promise, when ye knocked them senseless by His permission, until ye showed cowardice, and wrangled, and rebelled, after he had shown you what ye loved. Amongst you are those who love this world, and amongst you are those who love the next. Then He turned you away from them to try you; but He has pardoned you, for God is Lord of grace unto believers"